<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-F7D649A2-5E35-4CBD-BD9F-69ECD8344582" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-F7D649A2-5E35-4CBD-BD9F-69ECD8344582" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">04 The process of the printhead</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">5 Printheads are used in this printer. Each color has 1 printhead. The 5 printheads and 3 dummy printheads are positioned in the printhead carriage. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-5C339A3A-DBE1-4677-A0D2-9E3F5905763E"><title class="- topic/title ">The printhead(s) (marked in yellow) </title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-FF11634C-F15D-46B2-86BE-5B760657BF4F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-FF11634C-F15D-46B2-86BE-5B760657BF4F-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In the printhead carriage the printheads are indicated from 6 to 1 (from the left to the right hand side). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each printhead has 512 nozzles divided in 4 arrays (2 arrays per MEMS chip). Each array has 128 nozzles. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The system has 5 printheads with 2560 nozzles in total. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Overview of the numbering of the printheads (PHx), arrays (Ax) and nozzles. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-2C086CD2-37CB-4208-A76C-D55217DAF6D6"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-5DAFCE8D-D499-44C7-91FC-0400E0C8A3EF-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-5DAFCE8D-D499-44C7-91FC-0400E0C8A3EF-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="SECTION_17A4E8E110E14D75BBC12F1A41F46AD0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The printhead</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printhead consist of the of the following parts: 
</p><fig id="GUID-9858A6A2-851C-469C-A10F-D4D84580029B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-0ACB0D82-928B-4476-8292-6974264FAB79-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0ACB0D82-928B-4476-8292-6974264FAB79-low.png"/></fig><ul id="UL_890B25E7C6C04707995A6E5B416FC3ED" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_A77000B59CA443BA9DFF27DDA5BE593F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Printhead PBA (1). 
</p></li><li id="LI_37B6232EAC6D49B096A9D0CABC0F3932" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Boiler Filter Unit (BFU) (2). 
</p></li><li id="LI_F1CEB98B511F4BE7A3755849EA3BFD20" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Ink Reservoir (IR) (3). 
</p></li><li id="LI_CC58F9E908DD4DB7AB5F5E40FCF27CAA" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Droplet Forming Unit (DFU) (4). 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="SECTION_96AB37EB051745F8BD9E1CC801AE55F3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The Printhead PBA</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Printhead PBA (1) consists of 8 ASIC’s and MPGA driver (MPGA (Mask Programmable Gate Array) is an integrated circuit developed for a particular use). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">An air duct (2) is positioned over the PBA to cool the 8 ASIC's (ASIC (Application Specific Integrated Circuits) is an integrated circuit developed for a particular use). 
</p><fig id="GUID-621E9562-1C88-4F9A-BD9E-141BABC37CB0" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-ED442A9E-F844-4EED-9409-6A11F78FCE99-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-ED442A9E-F844-4EED-9409-6A11F78FCE99-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The cooling fan (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Y motion system carriage cool 1 fan</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05M2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">YMS_CAR_COOL1_FAN</compsignal></comp>) is used to cool all 5 Printhead PBA's. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_3CB65BB626604B42BFF44091BCADD3B7" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Boiler Unit (BU)</title><ul id="UL_881AA01DD84349799072AEB81641F0B3" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_2E965C154F0D4955BF7DE122593AB76D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Boiler heats up the ink 
</p></li><li id="LI_C2E672C551F84529825ACF3E629BC866" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Heater (1) and NTC (2) are mounted in the boiler unit 
</p></li><li id="LI_17E7048009C84896AE298D3505DC99C4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Boiler: ink tube (3) connected to boiler unit 
</p></li><li id="LI_0BE7F7DB335F402DA682741AD4120F76" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Primary filter (4) 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-7A700D8B-225E-40A7-A114-E27491AC09F4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9A78C9B2-8B02-4461-8CED-83E7366634BA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9A78C9B2-8B02-4461-8CED-83E7366634BA-low.png"/></fig><note id="GUID-B9E60138-FBAE-42A8-A5A9-E74C9104000C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The boiler unit can be replaced by a trained service technician. 
</p></note></section><section id="SECTION_9E9033EA3B394B6CAB520D93284A0E44" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Ink Reservoir (IR)</title><ul id="UL_8B2FD55CD8744984A91285AAE3F786AE" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_82CCB9A7F34F463096BE4F8043A84FDF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">NTC (1) and Heater (2) to heat up the ink 
</p></li><li id="LI_CE64FC2C55C246D7BF0C4659C4EC9259" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Air tube (3) supplied to ink reservoir. Pressure supplied: – 10 mbar +/- 2 mbar 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Level sensor (4): low and high, capacity detectors 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-043FC483-34B0-413E-8A0D-2F810B52EFAA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-44F7E569-20E9-4FA1-9364-CDDBC51F0B6C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-44F7E569-20E9-4FA1-9364-CDDBC51F0B6C-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_4A3C909878ED464A8FAD61BE9CF684F2" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Droplet Forming Unit (DFU) </title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Top part</b> 
</p><ul id="UL_37866660D822430F9B73919F7EBDBE6D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_28198D0D009D4853957F84F65329262E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Heater and NTC 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Temperature +/- 80 degree Celsius (printing and standby) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Temperature +/- 42 degree Celsius (standby and low power mode) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Secondary filter 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bottom part</b> 
</p><ul id="UL_9E22515931F249EC9C35E93669FB860E" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_76D8B72368CC4945855967FBFB6195AA" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flex bundle (1) 
</p></li><li id="LI_DC6ED90AB38E440E94041B2215FEBCE8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Two MEMS-chips (2) 
</p></li><li id="LI_8BB1204A63604968831685FB41AC573A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Front Finish Plate (3) 
</p></li><li id="LI_2F0C19F9A7DB44A0BEDBB7484AB64966" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Two position balls (4) 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-1554EC9F-3D26-439B-BA5C-1EFE12A7D6F8" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E049B43A-5284-4607-92AD-949EC33633DD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E049B43A-5284-4607-92AD-949EC33633DD-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_4F55901027C2463D967AC0C3F3798831" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Principle of the MEMS/Piezo technology</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printhead of the system is piezo based. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Piezo electricity describes the interaction of mechanical force and electrical current. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This technology can be used in two directions. 
</p><ul id="UL_383A93FC9902495CB4DAF030B332AF2C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_966C1DA165734C58A3FFA40B45B115FF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Applying force on a piezo electric material creates an electrical current 
</p></li><li id="LI_826715B5E37D4F718D964DE0DC86119F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Applying an electrical current on a piezo electric material creates a mechanical deformation in a piezo material. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Famous application of option one is a cigarette lighter where a mechanical force produces a voltage that ignites the gas. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The second option is used in piezo inkjet technology. The mechanical deformation is used to decrease the volume of a small room or channel in such a manner that a droplet of ink is ejected. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-DED869E2-6BF4-4A33-A12A-F3C8CD878DCF.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
